     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="16"/>
   <head>To his very worshipfull, an<gap reason="illegible" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>
deare Cousing, the Laird
of Boine.</head>
   <l>THe Gut which <hi>Vulcan</hi> forged in his yre,</l>
   <l>To punish those which follow <hi>Venus</hi> way,</l>
   <l>Can finde nothing to quench that flaming fyre,</l>
   <l>So fit as fine <hi>Tabacco</hi> sundrie say,</l>
   <l>For proofe of which great Pillar of my kin</l>
   <l>Tell what thou knowest: for to conceale were sin</l>
   <pb facs="16"/>
</div>
